    <abstract>Delivered by the Indian Queen Śrīmālā 勝鬘夫人, the daughter of King Prasenajit 波斯匿王. No
        Sanskrit has survived, but a Tibetan translation. The notion of tathāgatagarbha as the
        source of all dharmas is introduced in this text, and then taken up as a central topic in
        such texts as the Ratnagotravibhāga 寶性論, the Laṅkâvatāra-sūtra 楞伽經, the Awakening of
        Mahāyāna Faith 大乘起信論, etc. It has been translated into English in by Alex Wayman (1974) and
        by Diana Paul (2008). </abstract>
